<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-14-0041 </DOCNO><TEXT>The authors designed and implemented a totally digital picture archivingand communication system (PACS) in the pediatric radiology unit at theirinstitution. Conventional radiographic images are acquired in digitalformat using a Fuji computed radiographic system. Two laser scannersare used to digitize old existing comparison films. Image storage isaccomplished using both magnetic and digital optical disks. For display,the system supports three viewing stations: one 512 x 512 station withsix video monitors, one, 1,024 x 1,024 station with three monitors, andone 1,440 x 1,440 monitor.</TEXT></DOC>